### isLocationSpill() {#a7c448361f7ab2e7e44f0754b221d1428}

### transferSpillOrRestoreInst() {#adf45901cb1b75b061ca31e7400201794}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void VarLocBasedLDV::transferSpillOrRestoreInst (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp; MI, OpenRangesSet &amp; OpenRanges, VarLocMap &amp; VarLocIDs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">TransferMap</a> &amp; Transfers)</>}>
A spilled register may indicate that we have to end the current range of a variable and create a new one for the spill location.

A restored register may indicate the reverse situation. We don&#39;t want to insert any instructions in process(), so we just create the DBG&#95;VALUE without inserting it and keep track of it in <code>Transfers</code>. It will be inserted into the BB when we&#39;re done iterating over the instructions.
